1
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,360
You're the only one I love.

2
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,280
OFFLINE

3
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:03,760
Why can't I access the CCTV at home?

4
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:05,480
Three-zero-five.

5
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,080
Yes.

6
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:13,200
You need to be very careful.

7
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:14,800
Because that lieutenant

8
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,680
died a long time ago.

9
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,400
All that's left now is the commander
you have to deal with.

10
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:24,400
I'd like to invite you to come give
a statement at police headquarters.

11
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,840
Give a statement?

12
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:27,720
Don't contact me again.

13
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,960
So you're just going to throw me away?

14
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:30,560
Go find someone else to help you.

15
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:31,760
You fucking bastard!

16
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,920
Mr. Samut!

17
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,000
Samut was the one who let me in.

18
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:37,040
No! No!

19
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,760
You can't move, huh?

20
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:39,920
No!

21
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:42,440
No… hey!

22
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:57,520
You dare slap me?

23
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,200
You dare slap me?

24
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,360
Slap me?

25
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,280
You dare slap me?

26
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:18,320
No. Let me go.

27
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:20,959
- No!
- Maysa.

28
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:22,880
- Maysa.
- No!

29
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,920
Wayu.

30
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,080
Thank you for helping me.

31
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:38,680
Consider this my payment to Black Doc.

32
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,240
He said I've got the bid in the bag.

33
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:52,360
- No need to worry about it.
- Mm.

34
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:54,000
Just wait for the good news.

35
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:01,000
But your wife and father-in-law…

36
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:03,840
They're not gonna be a problem, right?

37
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,480
So what if they are?

38
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:13,520
Those two can't do anything to us anyway.

39
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:18,480
We could spend the money from this project
for generations.

40
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:23,800
Throw them a few scraps,
and they should already be grateful.

41
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,320
Yeah.

42
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:36,960
Where are you gonna run?

43
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:40,920
I've got money.

44
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:44,800
You don't want money?

45
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:18,320
Is our PR taking good care of Mr. Jiang?

46
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:23,560
Didn't you have Ms. Fahsai
entertain Mr. Jiang tonight, sir?

47
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,040
What did you just say?

48
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,200
Wait.

49
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,440
Fahsai's here right now?

50
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,120
You didn't know, sir?

51
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,040
Why the hell didn't you call and check?

52
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:39,960
Move!

53
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,880
Where is she?

54
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:42,720
The Diamond VIP room, sir.

55
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,520
How could you let this happen?

56
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,680
You still wanna fight me?

57
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,440
What strength
do you think you've got left?

58
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:51,280
Hey!

59
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,120
Fahsai!

60
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,120
What did you do to my sister?

61
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:08,520
Dad.

62
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,040
You touched my daughter.

63
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,400
Die!

64
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,520
- Fahsai.
- You!

65
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,680
- Fahsai.
- You!

66
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:17,880
You!

67
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,960
- You!
- Fahsai.

68
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:21,520
You!

69
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:34,960
Mr. Rakchart! Mr. Rakchart!

70
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:37,160
Dad!

71
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:38,680
Mr. Rakchart.

72
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:44,680
- What the hell did you do to my daughter?
- Dad, stop!

73
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,160
Wayu saved me.

74
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,800
He came to help me.

75
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:52,360
The one who drugged me

76
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:56,640
and tried to sell me off to another man
was that bastard husband of mine.

77
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:58,040
What did you just say?

78
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,320
Samut…

79
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,640
He tricked me.

80
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:08,720
He pretended to be kind,
so I'd let my guard down and trust him,

81
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,760
then he drugged me.

82
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:15,440
He handed me over to the man
who was going to give him the contract.

83
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,560
He treated me like I wasn't even human,

84
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:22,880
like I was just some pet, Dad.

85
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,360
Then how did you end up
helping my daughter?

86
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:37,480
Dr. Sakda and I
know each other pretty well.

87
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:42,440
He told me Samut
had brought him a special offer,

88
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:45,120
but even he didn't expect him

89
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:50,440
to trade his own wife

90
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:52,960
for a contract.

91
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,800
Thank you for saving my daughter.

92
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,160
It's nothing.

93
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:10,320
We might get to help
each other again soon.

94
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:16,560
Sir. Hurry up.

95
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:18,440
- Sir.
- Be careful.

96
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,840
- Sir.
- Excuse me.

97
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,400
Sir.

98
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:23,320
This way.

99
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,800
Be careful.

100
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,000
This way.

101
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,400
Jon, take care of Dad.

102
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,480
Yes, boss.

103
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:40,280
Fahsai, Fahsai.

104
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:43,120
Fahsai.

105
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,160
What is it, Sam?

106
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:54,880
This is bad. Ms. Fahsai…

107
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,360
What happened to Fahsai?

108
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:22,480
Fahsai went to Heaven Club.
What the hell did you do to her?

109
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:25,480
And who the hell are you
to meddle in my family's business?

110
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:29,160
Fahsai is my wife.
That makes her my family too.

111
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,480
Yeah?

112
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:36,880
Please calm down.

113
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,800
This is a hospital. Don't fight here.

114
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:41,360
- Please calm down.
- Please.

115
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,720
Ms. Fahsai's family?

116
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:48,760
The patient's awake now.
We're about to move her to a room.

117
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:56,200
All done.

118
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:58,640
- Please get some rest now, okay?
- I'm okay, thank you.

119
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:19,640
I want to talk to my brother alone.

120
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:37,680
So…

121
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:42,320
the rumors about the secret rooms
at Heaven Club were true after all.

122
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,920
How could you do this?

123
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,440
How could you force women

124
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:52,920
who are the same
as your mother and sister to do that?

125
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,280
Fahsai,

126
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:59,520
you're misunderstanding things.

127
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:05,520
The clients at the club
are all high-profile people.

128
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:10,040
Nobody's forcing anyone.
Plenty of women want to work there.

129
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:13,640
Then what about me?

130
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:19,640
Look at what happened to me first

131
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,400
before you say that.

132
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,960
Say it like a man. Admit that
you force those women into prostitution.

133
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,840
That was just one woman, Fahsai.

134
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:36,640
At first, she agreed willingly,

135
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,200
then suddenly she changed her mind.

136
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:42,400
Then why did you have to use force?

137
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:45,600
I didn't force anyone. Nobody did.

138
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:51,160
She played hard to get
because she wanted more money.

139
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:56,480
The club paid her
exactly what she asked for.

140
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:01,040
Like I said, everything
can be solved with money.

141
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,120
Then,

142
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,440
how much should I be paid?

143
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:28,080
Can you put a price on me too?

144
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:37,240
I think you should never go there again.

145
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:40,520
Like the woman named Peekul?

146
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,640
I don't know anyone by that name.

147
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:50,160
Stop lying already!

148
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:00,360
- Wait, Fahsai.
- Stop!

149
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:04,160
Don't touch me.

150
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:08,240
I can't stand being near you
even for another second.

151
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:11,480
Wayu,

152
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:17,000
take me away from this hell.

153
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:11,080
You never should've put yourself
in danger like that.

154
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:14,240
And if I hadn't gone,

155
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:19,920
would I ever have known
my father and brother

156
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,840
were capable of something so horrible?

157
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:31,440
And what if you'd gotten hurt
even worse than this?

158
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:35,320
Have you ever thought
about how that would've made me feel?

159
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:49,000
Do I really matter that much to you?

160
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:54,720
Why would you say that?

161
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,600
You're my wife.

162
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:05,080
You're my family.

163
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,360
You know…

164
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:20,560
When you smile like that,

165
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,720
it reminds me of someone.

166
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:30,040
He was very kind to me.

167
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:42,360
And I wish…

168
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:49,040
I wish I could see him again someday.

169
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:03,320
Don't think too much right now.

170
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:07,720
You need to focus on getting better first.

171
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:27,520
Sorry about your father and sister.

172
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:30,800
But you had it coming.

173
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:35,240
You've hurt so many people.
Karma finally caught up with you.

174
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:37,280
What are you talking about?

175
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:39,920
You think you own the world?
You can do whatever you want?

176
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:43,760
I've been your damn servant for years.

177
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:46,040
Cleaning up all your messes.

178
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,880
And you dared to do this to my daughter?

179
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:50,440
You sent my daughter to sleep with
another man,

180
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:51,880
even though she's your wife.

181
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:58,240
If your sister got violated
by someone else, then she deserved it.

182
00:18:58,320 --> 00:18:59,360
You bastard!

183
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:06,800
You dare hit me?

184
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,640
Not only am I gonna hit you,

185
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:11,400
I'm gonna expose you too.

186
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:14,360
I'm gonna ruin you.

187
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:37,080
Have you ever seen anyone else as human?

188
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:40,440
Or are my daughter and I just dogs to you?

189
00:19:57,840 --> 00:19:59,960
Running for your life like a damn dog?

190
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:01,560
So you're scared of dying too?

191
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:06,400
If you don't wanna die,
then crawl to my feet and beg me.

192
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:07,960
Come on!

193
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,040
Boss, move!

194
00:20:57,920 --> 00:21:00,880
Get the damn car! Go after him!

195
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:50,120
- Hello, Ms. Maysa.
- Yes.

196
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,840
What is it, Captain?

197
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:55,080
Where is your father?

198
00:21:57,320 --> 00:21:59,520
We have an arrest warrant for him.

199
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,400
We need him to come to the station.

200
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,640
My father isn't here.

201
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:19,440
Please cooperate with us.

202
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:22,080
You should convince him
to turn himself in.

203
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,520
He really isn't here.

204
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:32,080
And I don't know where he went either.

205
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,920
Captain,

206
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:40,800
we've received reports of gunshots
fired at Minister Rakchart's house.

207
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:43,400
Witnesses also saw
Commander Singha's car leaving the scene.

208
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:47,480
Excuse us.

209
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:52,400
Alert all nearby units.
I want updates immediately.

210
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:53,480
Yes, sir.

211
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:58,720
Go.

212
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:27,920
Wait.

213
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:31,120
You go that way.

214
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:22,240
You're out of bullets,
aren't you, Commander?

215
00:26:22,320 --> 00:26:23,640
Black Doc.

216
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:26,200
I can treat that wound on your leg.

217
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:27,920
But I'll need something in return.

218
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:29,960
What do you want?

219
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:31,240
The truth.

220
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:35,400
You have to confess
to everything you've done.

221
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:53,440
Wayu!

222
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:58,040
Why are you so shocked?
You suspected it was me all along.

223
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:03,400
That's why you sent your daughter
to steal my hair for a DNA test.

224
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:07,280
I didn't do anything wrong.
What the hell am I supposed to confess to?

225
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:09,680
You tried to kill me, Uncle,

226
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:14,400
so Mahasamut could get away

227
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:17,360
with killing Mom and Peekul.

228
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:43,800
You have no idea

229
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:47,840
what I had to do to get to this day.

230
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:49,680
Peeraka?

231
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:52,240
Sharp as ever.

232
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:59,640
Wait. Calm down.

233
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:01,600
Should I kill you right now,

234
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:07,040
or give you a chance to confess?

235
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:09,520
Calm down.

236
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:14,120
Listen to me first.

237
00:28:23,040 --> 00:28:26,440
I'm a civilian.
How would I have a real gun?

238
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:30,120
Unlike Mahasamut,

239
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:33,840
he definitely has one.

240
00:28:35,320 --> 00:28:36,720
Since you refuse to confess,

241
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:40,080
go ahead and face your fate.

242
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:17,400
Finish him.

243
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:45,400
<i>We received a report</i>
<i>of gunshots near the exit.</i>

244
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:47,880
Copy that.

245
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:30,920
You were planning to expose me with this?

246
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:39,000
Then…

247
00:30:40,160 --> 00:30:41,720
I'll send it off with you.

248
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:48,760
Do it.

249
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:16,320
Take care of his house too.

250
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:32,640
Dispatch, this is 02.

251
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:36,560
The suspect's car is on fire.
The suspect's car is on fire.

252
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:48,760
Dad!

253
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:52,440
- Dad!
- Ms. Maysa, don't go in.

254
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:53,440
- Dad!
- Ms. Maysa.

255
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,640
It's dangerous. Don't go in.

256
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:55,560
- Dad!
- Ms. Maysa.

257
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:58,360
Stay here. Don't go in. It's dangerous.

258
00:32:58,440 --> 00:33:00,760
- Stay here.
- Dad!

259
00:33:03,040 --> 00:33:04,400
- Dad!
- Calm down.

260
00:33:08,680 --> 00:33:10,400
It's because of me.

261
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:13,600
You ended up like this because of me.

262
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:28,320
It's Samut. Samut did this.

263
00:33:28,400 --> 00:33:30,400
It wasn't an accident.

264
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:32,040
He did it

265
00:33:32,120 --> 00:33:34,600
because Dad had just gone
to settle things with him.

266
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:37,000
Ms. Maysa, don't worry.

267
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:38,920
I'll investigate this thoroughly.

268
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:41,200
That bastard.

269
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:44,960
I will drag him into prison myself.

270
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:48,000
He has to be punished!

271
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:11,560
The patient's hypertension
hasn't been well controlled.

272
